The paper discusses the use of traditional AI reasoning techniques for coordinating teams of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in dynamic environments, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the challenges of communication among distributed agents, which suggests a focus on Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of ASP for agent architecture and reasoning algorithms suggests a focus on Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The application of the architecture to UAVs in dynamic environments suggests a focus on Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
